headline: Broadcom earnings, November PPI, mortgage rates: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime co-hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton break down the key events investors should monitor on Thursday, December 12. On the earnings front, investors will closely watch results from three top companies: Broadcom (AVGO), Costco Wholesale (COST), and Lennar (LEN). The November Producer Price Index (PPI) is set to be released, with economists anticipating core PPI to increase by 0.2%. In the afternoon, Freddie Mac will publish its weekly Mortgage Rates report, providing an updated snapshot of the housing finance market. Additionally, President-elect Donald Trump is scheduled to ring the opening bell at the New York Stock Exchange. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Angel Smith
